      • addLikeFilter

        public void addLikeFilter(@Nullable
                          java.lang.String fieldName,
                          @Nullable
                          java.lang.Object value)
        Adds a "like" filter.

        Note:

        - if the value is not a String or a list/array, then the "like" filter behaves like the "equal" filter. Similar to addEqualFilter(String, Object)

        - if the value is a String, it can be either a substring, a Java Regex or an SQL like entry

        - if the value is a list/array, the filter checks if any element of the list is verified (equivalent of an OR of LIKE filters).

        Parameters:
        fieldName - field name to apply the filter on
        value - the value of the filter
